headline: Nature Medicine Publishes Helus Pharma’s Randomized, Placebo-Controlled Phase 2a Trial of SPL026 in Major Depressive Disorder
summary: Randomized, placebo-controlled Phase 2a study of SPL026 met its primary endpoint demonstrating a clinically significant reduction in depressive symptoms as measured by MADRS score (mean difference: -7.35) versus placebo at two weeksAntidepressant treatment effects observed within one week and sustained for up to three months Findings reinforce the therapeutic potential of short-acting serotonergic agonists and inform Helus Pharma’s HLP004 development program, with Phase 2 topline data in general
